article.headline: Cal Poly 98, Santa Clara 89
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Nick Enzweiler was a perfect 6 of 6 from three-point range as Cal Poly got its first win of the season with a 98-89 upset of Santa Clara. Enzweiler, who scored just 10 points in the first four games, came off the bench with 22 points, seven rebounds and five assists. The senior forward was also a perfect 4 of 4 from the free-throw line. Cal Poly, which used a different starting lineup for the fifth straight game, shot 61.2 percent in the game and never trailed after Mike Titchenal hit a jumper that gave the Mustangs a 47-45 lead a couple minutes into the second half. Freshman guard Dawin Whiten had a team-high 26 points for the Mustangs (1-4). Santa Clara (6-3), which beat North Carolina and Stanford earlier this year, was led by Kyle Bailey's 29 points. Fernando Sampson, who had not played this season because of an ankle injury, returned to score 11 points for Cal Poly. Teammate Phil Johnson added 17 points as four Mustangs reach double figures.
